      "message": "Based on current Linux kernel used by Chrome OS ( https://source.chromium.org/chromiumos/chromiumos/codesearch/+/master:src/third_party/kernel/v5.4/drivers/power/supply/power_supply_sysfs.c;l\u003d42-46 ), there are two power types (UPS and BrickID) in addition to the lists in autotest ( https://source.chromium.org/chromiumos/chromiumos/codesearch/+/master:src/third_party/autotest/files/client/cros/power/power_status.py;l\u003d423-424;drc\u003de3bde74b98148a3302be4e3b91644c7687bc928e ).\n\nBrickID is for Apple charger\nhttps://patchwork.kernel.org/patch/9716761/\n\nand UPS stands for Uninterruptible Power Supply.\nhttps://elinux.org/images/4/45/Power-supply_Sebastian-Reichel.pdf\n\nSo I decided to add these two types to this list.",
